Community Engagement Strategy
Emory’s new Community Engagement Strategy seeks to make a deeper impact in Atlanta and Georgia through its continued work to identify, address, and solve challenges in our city and state with our community partners. To do this, we will be concentrating on three areas of focus: social and economic mobility; health and well-being; and arts, science, and cultural enrichment.
Artwork by Emory students in the
Arts and Social Justice Fellows
program.
